        <h2>1. Eligibility and Account Registration</h2>
        <h3>1.1 Eligibility</h3>
        <p>You must be at least eighteen (18) years of age and possess the legal capacity to enter into binding agreements to use the Platform. If you are accessing the Platform on behalf of a business entity, you represent and warrant that you are authorized to accept these Terms on behalf of that entity.</p>

        <h3>1.2 Account Creation</h3>
        <p>To access the Platform, you must create an account and provide accurate, current, and complete registration information. You agree to promptly update your account information to keep it accurate and current. Each legal entity may maintain only one organization account; multiple individual user accounts within an organization are permitted and encouraged.</p>

        <h3>1.3 Account Security</h3>
        <p>You are solely responsible for maintaining the confidentiality of your account credentials, including your password and any two-factor authentication devices. You agree to notify BuildWorkPro immediately at <a href={`mailto:${config.email.security}`}>{config.email.security}</a> of any unauthorized use of your account or any other breach of security. BuildWorkPro shall not be liable for any loss or damage arising from your failure to maintain the security of your account credentials.</p>

        <h3>1.4 Organizational Administration</h3>
        <p>Organization administrators are responsible for managing user access within their organization, including inviting and removing team members, assigning roles (Administrator, Manager, Member, Field Crew, or Viewer), and configuring permission settings. Administrators assume responsibility for the actions of users they invite to the organization.</p>

        <h2>2. Subscription, Fees, and Payment</h2>
        <h3>2.1 Subscription Plans</h3>
        <p>The Platform is offered on a subscription basis. Current pricing is seventy-nine U.S. dollars ($79.00) per month or seven hundred ninety U.S. dollars ($790.00) per year (annual billing, which includes two months at no additional charge). All subscriptions include unlimited users, unlimited projects, and access to all Platform features.</p>

        <h3>2.2 Free Trial</h3>
        <p>New accounts receive a fourteen (14) day free trial with full access to all Platform features. No credit card or payment information is required to begin the trial. At the conclusion of the trial period, a paid subscription is required to continue using the Platform. If you do not subscribe, your account will be suspended but your data will be retained for thirty (30) days.</p>

        <h3>2.3 Billing and Renewal</h3>
        <p>Subscriptions renew automatically at the end of each billing cycle (monthly or annually) unless canceled prior to the renewal date. All fees are charged in advance and are billed through our third-party payment processor, Stripe, Inc. You authorize BuildWorkPro to charge your designated payment method for all applicable fees.</p>

        <h3>2.4 Cancellation and Refunds</h3>
        <p>You may cancel your subscription at any time through the billing section of your account settings. Upon cancellation:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Your subscription remains active through the end of the current paid billing period.</li>
          <li>You retain full access to the Platform until the end of that period.</li>
          <li>No partial refunds are issued for unused portions of a billing period, except as described below.</li>
        </ul>
        <p>Refund requests submitted within the first thirty (30) days of an initial paid subscription will be honored in full. After thirty (30) days, no refunds will be issued. Refund requests should be directed to <a href={`mailto:${config.email.support}`}>{config.email.support}</a>.</p>

        <h3>2.5 Price Changes</h3>
        <p>We reserve the right to modify subscription pricing upon thirty (30) days&rsquo; prior written notice to the email address associated with your account. Price changes will take effect at the start of the next billing cycle following the notice period. Annual subscriptions are honored at their contracted rate for the duration of the then-current annual term.</p>

        <h3>2.6 Taxes</h3>
        <p>All fees are exclusive of applicable taxes, levies, or duties imposed by taxing authorities. You are responsible for payment of all such taxes (excluding taxes based on BuildWorkPro&rsquo;s net income), and we may collect applicable sales tax where legally required.</p>

